errors.MAE: Mean Absolute Error. The average of the absolute values of all errors (the closer to 0, the better the model).
errors.MSE: Mean Squared Error. The average of the squared errors (difference between predicted and actual values).
errors.RMSE: Root Mean Squared Error. The average difference between the predicted and actual values in the model. It estimates how well the model predicts the target value (accuracy).
errors.R2: R² (Coefficient of Determination) is a metric that evaluates the performance of a regression model by indicating how well the model explains the given data. It ranges from 0 to 1, with values closer to 1 indicating a better fit.

performance.F1_SCORE: F1 Score. A performance metric that balances precision and recall (values range from 0 to 1, with higher values being better).
performance.ACCURACY: Accuracy. A metric that evaluates how accurately a classification model has classified the data.
